# style_guide.mdc

## Purpose
This rule defines the visual identity and styling standards for all generated dashboards and components, ensuring consistency with the company's futuristic gaming aesthetic and brand identity.

---

## Visual Style Guide & Brand Identity

### Core Design Philosophy
- **Futuristic Gaming Aesthetic**: Embrace a cyberpunk/gaming-inspired visual language with neon accents, grid patterns, and digital interfaces
- **Dark Mode First**: All dashboards should use dark backgrounds as the primary canvas
- **Precision & Technical Excellence**: Clean, minimal layouts that emphasize data clarity and professional sophistication

### Color Palette

#### Primary Colors
- **Background**: Deep black (#000000) or very dark gray (#0a0a0a)
- **Surface**: Dark gray (#1a1a1a) for cards and containers
- **Border**: Subtle gray (#333333) for outlines and dividers

#### Accent Colors
- **Primary Blue**: Bright electric blue (#3b82f6 or #0066ff) for primary actions and highlights
- **Success Green**: Vibrant green (#10b981 or #00ff66) for positive metrics and growth indicators
- **Warning Orange**: Bright orange (#f59e0b or #ff6b35) for alerts and key insights
- **Error Red**: Vivid red (#ef4444 or #ff3333) for negative metrics and warnings

#### Text Colors
- **Primary Text**: Pure white (#ffffff) for headings and important data
- **Secondary Text**: Light gray (#a3a3a3) for descriptions and labels
- **Muted Text**: Medium gray (#666666) for metadata and less important info

### Typography
- **Headings**: Bold, sans-serif fonts (Helvetica, Arial, or system fonts)
- **Body Text**: Medium weight, clean readability
- **Data/Numbers**: Monospace or clean sans-serif for precise alignment
- **Size Hierarchy**: Clear distinction between heading levels (32px, 24px, 18px, 16px, 14px)

#### Text Usage Guidelines
- **Font Hierarchy**: Use consistent font weights (400, 500, 600, 700) throughout dashboard
- **High Contrast**: Maintain excellent contrast ratios (7:1 for AAA compliance)
- **Alignment**: Left-align body text, center-align key metrics and titles
- **Case Conventions**: Use sentence case for labels, title case for section headers

